recordedBy: M.J. Jansen-Jacobs; C. Feuillet, P. Hiepko, L. Skog, B.J.H. ter Welle
habitat: Along stream with sand and rocks in forest.
occurrenceRemarks: Tree to 10m tall; ca. 15cm in diameter. Young fruits green like figs. Mature fruit soft, juicy, velvety, golden yellow, resembling a ripe apricot. Leaves dull green above. Young branches soft brown. Tree leaning on a plam.
name: Eugenia armeniaca Sagot

recordedBy: M.J. Jansen-Jacobs; C. Feuillet, P. Hiepko, L. Skog, B.J.H. ter Welle
occurrenceRemarks: Tree, 7m x7cm. Sepals pale green. Fruit somewhat pear-shaped, 4.5 x 4cm, green, when mature yellow and soft.
name: Eugenia armeniaca Sagot
